Tomorrow start the first day back at YAE! Just some reminders to ensure the safety of all of our students...

Hello everyone! We have been busy at the school getting ready for the governors new order for all schools to be closed until May 1st.

This week you will be able to drop off your student(s) first learning packet and pick up the new learning resources for your student(s) Monday or Tuesday from 10-2. These resources will be for next week through spring break. The next learning resources will be available April 20 and 21.

If you have any questions, please message or call the school at (330)746-3970. Stay safe! üíôüíõüíô

We have a lot of incentives happening for our students if they turn in their re-enrollment forms and Proof of Residency (POR) by next Friday, January 31, 2020! Students who turn in their re-enrollment forms, whether you mark that your child will be back next year, won‚Äôt be back, or undecided, will be allowed to dress down every Friday until the end of the year üò± and have a movie and popcorn party in the gym! üéâ
The POR‚Äôs (Proof of Residency) are due February 12th and each student will be given a $5 Knight Knote to spend in our newly stocked store!! üíµ
A proof of residency can be a utility bill, gas bill, or Youngstown water bill (all three must be dated within 30 days) or a lease with your current address.
If you have any questions, please contact our enrollment specialist by calling the main office at (330)746-3970 and asking for Mrs. Orizal.

üéâREMINDER!üéâ

üíôThe end of the year field trip to Splash Lagoon is tomorrow (Friday, May 17, 2019)!
üíõStudents must have a swim suit and towel in order to go, Splash Lagoon does not provide towels anymore. Appropriate swimsuits for girls: one piece swimsuits or two piece swim suits that cover the midriff. Appropriate swimsuits for boys: swim trunks with or without a shirt. Keep in mind, some attractions do not allow T-Shirts or ‚Äúnon-swimwear‚Äù clothing.
üíôWe are not allowed to bring any food or drinks into the park. All students will eat lunch on the bus, be given a food voucher for dinner, and have snacks on the way home. If you would like to give your child money for additional food inside Splash Lagoon that is fine, however teachers and staff are not responsible for lost or stolen money.
üíõMake sure your children are on time for school! We are leaving by 9:30 AM, if not before. The field trip bus cannot wait for anyone.
üíôStudents should have a small bag or plastic bag for their extra clothes and to put their wet suit and towel inside.
